What is cloud computing?
on-demand delivery of computing services/resources like
1. IAAS
2. PAAS
3. SAAS
to the world is called cloud computing.
	
every cloud provider takes care of providing/managing the lifecycle operations on the resources they offer, which are
1. provisioning
2. deprovisioning
3. scale-out
4. scale-in
5. scale-up
6. scale-down
7. back-up
8. restore
9. start
10. stop
11. restart

There are lot of cloud providers are available in the market and different cloud providers offers different type of services to the world.
	
1. Amazon Web Services (AWS) cloud provider
	# IAAS 
	# PAAS & SAAS = The Third-party PaaS & SaaS products are offered by aws as an services

2. Google Cloud Provider (GCP)
	#technology company = they dont manufacture or produce software products
	# IAAS
	
3. Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) 
	#tech company
	it has PaaS also and SaaS products
	PaaS
	1. Oracle Weblogic Server
	2. Oracle Database
	3. MySql Server
	4. Java
	5. Oracle Integration Cloud (OIC)
	6. Oracle SoaSuite
	7. Oracle Service Bus
	SaaS
	1. PeopleSoft
	2. EBusiness Suite
	3. JDEdwards
	4. Oracle Applications
Their cloud platform is pretty strong in offerring PaaS and SaaS services, but there are poor at IAAS

4. Microsoft Azure
	#IAAS
	Sql Server
	Mail Exchange Server
	Teams
	Data bricks
